reviews.text:
Crystal Jade is a nice and decent Chinese restaurant with wide range of food.
The restaurant is located on B2 of Times Square, right on the floor exit from MTR.  The decoration here is nice, and the hygiene is clean here.This is a chain restaurant and it's good they keep their quality.
Food here is good and decent, and it will never disappoint you but don't expect any surprise here
Price is above normal but acceptable as its located in Causeway Bay area.  And you will have to pay for the tea and service charge

Depending on locations. The menus in different branches vary. We like the one in Causeway Bay Time Square. With super value "kids meal"😎 the spicy beef also yummy, beef quality good unaffected by being spicy. Service also good 👍
Terrible service and food. Some dishes were edible. But some of the food was raw and uncooked. Took forever to arrive and waiters had a bad attitude. Tables were sticky too.
Still able to maintain the food at about the same quality after many years
Good value with good taste for HK especially for the kids meal!
